gurmukhi: nmo eyk rUpy nmo eyk rUpy ]12]102]
transliteration: Namo Ek Roope, Namo Ek Roope||12||102||
translation: Salutation to the Lord of One Form, Salutation to the Lord of One Form. 12.102.
His Glory is inexpressible, His Excellence from the very beginning cannot be described.
Non-aligned, Unassailable and from the very beginning Unmanifested and Unestablished.
He is the Enjoyer in diverse guises, invincible from the very beginning and an Unassailable Entity.

gurmukhi: nmo eyk rUpy nmo eyk rUpy ]13]103]
transliteration: Namo Ek Roope, Namo Ek Roope||13||103||
translation: Salutation to the Lord of One Form; Salutation to the Lord of One Form.13.103.

gurmukhi: n nyhM n gyhM n sokM n swkM ]
transliteration: Na Nehan Na Gehan, Na Sokan Na Saakan||
translation: He is without love, without home, without sorrow and without relations.
He is in the Yond, He is Holy and Immaculate and He is Independent.

gurmukhi: n jwqM n pwqM n imqRM n mMqRy ]
transliteration: Na Jaatan Na Paatan, Na Mitran Na Mantre||
translation: He is without caste, without line, without friend and without adviser.

gurmukhi: nmo eyk qMqRy nmo eyk qMqRy ]14]104]
transliteration: Namo Ek Tantre, Namo Ek Tantre||14||104||
translation: Salutation to the One Lord in wrap and woof; Salutation to the One Lord in wrap and woof. 14.104.

gurmukhi: n DrmM n BrmM n srmM n bwky ]
transliteration: Na Dharamannd Na Bharamannd, Na Saramannd Na Saake||
translation: He is without religion, without illusion, without shyness and without relations.

gurmukhi: n brmM n crmM n krmM n bwky ]
transliteration: Na Baramannd Na Charamannd, Na Karamannd Na Baake||
translation: He is without coat of mail, without shield, without steps and without speech.

gurmukhi: n sqRM n imqRM n puqRM srUpy ]
transliteration: Na Satran Na Mitran Na Poutran Daroope||
translation: He is without enemy, without friend and without countenance of a son.

gurmukhi: nmo Awid rUpy nmo Awid rUpy ]15]105]
transliteration: Namo Aadh Roope, Namo Aadh Roope||15||105||
translation: Salutation to that Primal entity; Salutation to that Primal Entity.15.105.

gurmukhi: khUM kMj ky mMj ky Brm BUly ] khUM rMk ky rwj ky Drm AlUly ]
transliteration: Kahoon Kanj Ke Manj Ke Bharam Bhoole|| Kahoon Rank Ke Raaj Ke Dharam Aloole||
translation: Somewhere as a black bee Thou art engaged in the delusion of fragrance of the lotus. Somewhere Thou art describing the characteristics of a king and the poor.
